title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that finds all the purchases in the household appliances file for purchases made in october 2025. It should only include purchases for organisation which have more than 10 departments, also return the creditor name of these purchases as well as the price and the purchase line. Output in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a Wayang plan that queries the household appliances file to find purchases made in October 2025. Filter the results to include only organisations with more than 10 departments. For each matching purchase, return the creditor name, the price, and the purchase line. Output the results to a text file.

log.thoughts: Select textfile household_appliances for filtering by appliance names. Use factpurchases joined with creditor for creditor name and with department (and its organisation_id) to apply the >10 departments condition. Filter by invoice_date in 2025-10.

steps.detailed_description: Load the following data sources: factpurchases, department, creditor, and household_appliances text file. These inputs will be used to (a) identify purchases in October 2025, (b) determine organisation department counts, (c) fetch creditor names, and (d) provide the list of target appliance lines to filter against.
Join factpurchases with department on department_id to attach organisation_id to each purchase. Output: purchases enriched with organisation_id.
Join the enriched purchases with creditor on creditor_id to bring in creditor name. Output: purchases enriched with organisation_id and creditor name.

Filter the enriched purchases using three criteria: (a) invoice_date in October 2025, (b) invoice_line_descr matches any line in the household_appliances text file, and (c) organisation has more than 10 departments (derive this from the department table by counting departments per organisation and keep only those organisations with count > 10). Output: a dataset containing creditor name, invoice_line_price, and invoice_line_descr for matching purchases.
Write the final filtered results to a text file. The output should contain the creditor name, the price (invoice_line_price), and the purchase line (invoice_line_descr) for each matching purchase.

log.thoughts: We load all needed sources, perform two joins to enrich purchases with organisation and creditor data, then apply a multi-criteria filter (date, appliance line matching, and organisation size) before writing the required fields to a text file. This keeps the plan concise (5 steps) while preserving data lineage.

title: Class: StepHandler created step dependencies and queue

log.thoughts: Generated initial input-transformations step loading four data sources in parallel without linking to subsequent steps yet.

operations.udf: (t: ((org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record, org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record))) => { val left = t._1; val right = t._2; val purch_id = left.getField(0); val ord_id = left.getField(1); val dept_id = left.getField(2); val organisation_id = right.getField(1); (purch_id, ord_id, dept_id, organisation_id) }

log.thoughts: Created a first subplan: load factpurchases and department, join on department_id to attach organisation_id, and map to produce enriched purchase row. Ensured JDBC outputs are consumed as Records in UDFs.
Created step 2 binary join between factpurchases and department on department_id. Used simple key extractors in join UDFs. Ensured IDs continue from previous (1) and next is 3.

Constructed a basic plan for step 4 by reusing step 2-3 inputs as per the dependencies. Implemented a simplistic October 2025 date filter and integrated appliances lines from the text source. The plan adheres to the required operator types and dependencies, with JDBC outputs receiving Record data as per the critical rule.
